{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "## Avoid hardcoding /machine:x64 flag on 64-bit on MSVC\r\n\r\nOn MSVC compilers with 64-bit, a /machine:x64 linker flag was manually added to workaround for http://www.cmake.org/Bug/print_bug_page.php?bug_id=11240 . However, that CMake bug was fixed in CMake 3.4, and the minimum version of CMake required by ignition-cmake is 3.5.1, so the workaround can be safely removed.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, now MSVC also supports compiling for ARM64 architecture (whose linker flag is /machine:ARM64) so the workaround is currently preventing the compilation of ignition libraries for ARM64 architectures with Visual Studio.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<h2 id=\"markdown-header-avoid-hardcoding-machinex64-flag-on-64-bit-on-msvc\">Avoid hardcoding /machine:x64 flag on 64-bit on MSVC</h2>\n<p>On MSVC compilers with 64-bit, a /machine:x64 linker flag was manually added to workaround for <a href=\"http://www.cmake.org/Bug/print_bug_page.php?bug_id=11240\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://www.cmake.org/Bug/print_bug_page.php?bug_id=11240</a> . However, that CMake bug was fixed in CMake 3.4, and the minimum version of CMake required by ignition-cmake is 3.5.1, so the workaround can be safely removed.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, now MSVC also supports compiling for ARM64 architecture (whose linker flag is /machine:ARM64) so the workaround is currently preventing the compilation of ignition libraries for ARM64 architectures with Visual Studio.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Merge 1 -> 2 (pull request #168)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Merge 1 -&gt; 2 (<a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/168/avoid-hardcoding-machine-x64-flag-on-64\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #168</a>)</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "## Avoid hardcoding /machine:x64 flag on 64-bit on MSVC\r\n\r\nOn MSVC compilers with 64-bit, a /machine:x64 linker flag was manually added to 